article.description: — Kaleb Hunter had 15 points off the bench to lift UNC Greensboro to a 68-49 win over Western Carolina on Monday night.
article.headline: Hunter lifts UNC Greensboro past W. Carolina 68-49
article.linkText: Hunter lifts UNC Greensboro past W. Carolina 68-49
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- — Kaleb Hunter had 15 points off the bench to lift UNC Greensboro to a 68-49 win over Western Carolina on Monday night. De'Monte Buckingham had 14 points for UNC Greensboro (14-10, 6-6 Southern Conference). Keyshaun Langley added 14 points and six rebounds. Bas Leyte had 10 rebounds. Nick Robinson had 20 points for the Catamounts (9-16, 3-9). Cam Bacote added 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
